eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 18 Years
Maximum age: 60 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.
The planned radiation therapy treatment dose must meet protocol requirements (Resected tumors/post-operative patients: maximum planned dose 66 Gy; Unresected tumors: maximum planned dose 70 Gy)
Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group (ECOG) performance status (PS) 2, 3, or 4

groups.description: Participants with relapsed or refractory DLBCL will receive 18 weeks of induction treatment. Venetoclax will be administered at the RP2D identified during the dose-escalation phase, in addition to polatuzumab vedotin and rituximab. Those who achieve CR or PR at the EOI will be eligible to receive an 8-month consolidation regimen consisting of venetoclax and rituximab.
groups.name: Expansion Cohort: DLBCL

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Descriptive statistics (summaries, distributions, 95% confidence intervals) will be reported and compared with the two arms in the randomized trial phase. Graphical displays will be used to show distributions (boxplots, density curves).
outcome_measures.measure: Percent of patients receiving genomic testing later in treatment (Aim I observational phase)

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Will be graphically summarized for the individual patients using a “swimmer plot” to convey the duration of treatment, timing of response and its duration, time until progression and survival. Descriptive statistics (mean, median, and 95% confidence intervals) will be utilized to present the exploratory efficacy results.
outcome_measures.time_frame: Time from registration to the earlier of progression or death due to any cause, assessed up to 2 years

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Induction: pre-infusion (0 hr) on Day 1 of Cycle 1; pre-infusion (within 5 hr prior to dose) on Day 1 on Cycles 2, 4; Post-induction: at treatment discontinuation (up to Month 24); 120 days and 1-2 years post-last dose (maximum up to 5 years) (infusion duration: 90 minutes) (1 cycle: 21 days)
outcome_measures.time_frame: Pre-infusion (0 hr) on Day 1 of Cycle 1 up to maximum 5 years. Detailed timeframe is given in outcome measure description.

outcome_measures.analysis_method:
Group A patient OR compared to Group B patient OR
Overall Remission includes Complete Remission (CR), Complete Remission with incomplete platelet recovery (CRp), Complete Remission with incomplete blood count recovery (CRi), and Partial Remission (PR). Complete remission means bone marrow blast count of less than 5% with adequate recovery of peripheral blood counts as typically defined by the IWG. Both CRi and CRp refer complete remission but with incomplete blood count and platelet recovery, respectively. PR, or partial remission, refers to remission in which bone marrow contains blast counts
outcome_measures.measure: Overall Remission (OR) Rate Based on the IWG Response Criteria
outcome_measures.time_frame: Up to 5 years or the duration of the study
